  "Which of the following is NOT a required axiom for an inner product <u, v> on a real vector space?": "",
  "Linearity in the first argument": "",
  "Positive definiteness: <v, v> >= 0, with equality iff v = 0": "",
  "Multiplicativity: <u, v> = <u, w><w, v>": "",
  "Symmetry: <u, v> = <v, u>": "",
  "An inner product must satisfy symmetry, linearity in one argument, and positive definiteness. There is no multiplicativity axiom for inner products.": "",
  "The standard inner product on R^n is the dot product <u, v> = u . v. What is <(1, 2, 3), (4, 5, 6)>?": "",
  "15": "",
  "21": "",
  "32": "",
  "38": "",
  "<(1,2,3),(4,5,6)> = 1*4 + 2*5 + 3*6 = 4 + 10 + 18 = 32.": "",
  "On the vector space of continuous functions on [0, 1], which of the following defines a valid inner product?": "",
  "<f, g> = max(f(x)) * max(g(x))": "",
  "<f, g> = integral from 0 to 1 of f(x)g(x) dx": "",
  "<f, g> = f(1) + g(1)": "",
  "<f, g> = f(0) * g(0)": "",
  "The integral inner product <f,g> = integral of f(x)g(x)dx on [0,1] satisfies all inner product axioms: symmetry, linearity, and positive definiteness (integral of f^2 >= 0, with equality only for f=0 in continuous functions).": "",
  "In an inner product space, the norm induced by the inner product is defined as ||v|| = ?": "",
  "<v, v>": "",
  "<v, v>^2": "",
  "sqrt(<v, v>)": "",
  "|<v, v>|": "",
  "The norm induced by an inner product is ||v|| = sqrt(<v, v>). This generalizes the familiar Euclidean norm ||v|| = sqrt(v . v) to abstract inner product spaces.": "",
  "The Cauchy-Schwarz inequality states that for any vectors u and v in an inner product space:": "",
  "<u, v> = ||u|| + ||v||": "",
  "|<u, v>| >= ||u|| * ||v||": "",
  "<u, v>^2 = ||u||^2 + ||v||^2": "",
  "|<u, v>| <= ||u|| * ||v||": "",
  "The Cauchy-Schwarz inequality |<u,v>| <= ||u|| ||v|| is one of the most fundamental results in inner product spaces. Equality holds if and only if u and v are linearly dependent.": "",
  "Consider the weighted inner product <u, v> = 2u1*v1 + 3u2*v2 on R^2. What is <(1, 1), (1, -1)>?": "",
  "1": "",
  "5": "",
  "0": "",
  "-1": "",
  "<(1,1),(1,-1)> = 2(1)(1) + 3(1)(-1) = 2 - 3 = -1.": "",
  "In an inner product space, two vectors u and v are orthogonal if and only if:": "",
