  "The L^2 inner product <f,g> = integral of f(x)g(x)dx on [0, pi] makes {sin(nx)} an orthogonal set because integral of sin(nx)sin(mx)dx = 0 for n != m by trigonometric identities.": "",
  "A machine learning researcher defines a kernel function K(x, y) that induces an inner product in a feature space. For vectors u = (1, 0) and v = (0, 1), if K(u, v) = 0 and K(u, u) = 2, what is the norm of u in the feature space?": "",
  "4, pa": "",
  "1, pa": "",
  "2, pa": "",
  "sqrt(2)": "",
  "In the feature space, the norm is ||u|| = sqrt(K(u, u)) = sqrt(2). The kernel function K implicitly defines an inner product in a potentially high-dimensional feature space.": "",
  "A quantum physicist works in a complex inner product space C^2. For states |a> = (1, i) and |b> = (i, 1), she computes <a|a>. What is the result?": "",
  "-2": "",
  "1 + i": "",
